        <updateDate>2021-07-20T20:54:52Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Promoting Effective and Empowering Recovery Services in Medicare Act of 2021 or the PEERS Act of </b><b>2021</b></p> <p>This bill specifies that peer support specialists may participate in the provision of behavioral health integration services with the supervision of a physician or other entity under Medicare. The bill defines <i>peer support specialists</i> as individuals who are recovering from a mental health or substance-use condition and have certain national or state credentials, as specified, to provide peer support services.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
